INSERT INTO `blogs` VALUES (1,'Welcome to our new blog','As you can see, we have a new blog now. A very simple one, but I hope it will get better over time.\r\n\r\nI see this blog as a possibility to communicate with you - the users of Eventicus. For now there is no comment functionality for blog posts, but i will add that within the next weeks.\r\n\r\nFirst I will tell you some facts about me and Eventicus. My name is Mathias KarstÃ¤dt (aka. webmatze) and I\'m a 30 years old male from Hanover, Germany. I am the developer of this social event community. Some of you will remember the first version of Eventicus. I coded it with PHP5 over a year ago. I had the idea for a website where everybody all over the world could add his or her events for free. I was not the only one with this idea. But I saw it as a private hobby project and did not made much advertising for it. But soon Eventicus was recognized by some people who then added links to there Web 2.0 lists. So over time a lot of people where using Eventicus although there where some bugs and it had not all functionality I wanted it to have.\r\n\r\nA few months ago I decided to start from zero and recode the entire system with Ruby On Rails. Thanks to this great framework I was able to come up with a new version of Eventicus within two months. The result is what you see here and I think it is much more simpler to use than the old version. There are still some features missing, but I will add them later. I have a lot of ideas for new functionalities but more about that in a later post. \r\n\r\nI know, some of you will hate it but i still call this a beta version. I hope that I get some feedback from you. If you find some bugs or have some suggestions for new features then leave a comment (with the yet to be added comment system). You can also use the Google Group Discussion:\r\nhttp://groups.google.com/group/eventicus/topics\r\n\r\nSo I thank you for now and hope to see you again here on Eventicus. And if you have got some events, don\'t hesitate to add them.\r\n\r\nYours faithfully\r\nMathias KarstÃ¤dt','2007-06-01 16:56:14',NULL,4),(2,'We have event photos now','As you might have noticed, everyone can add their own photos to every single event in Eventicus now.\r\n\r\nAll you need is an account at flickr.com and upload your event photos there. After that you should add a unique Eventicus event ID as a tag to your photos at flickr. You can find that ID for every event if you click on \"Add your own photos!\". The ID looks like \'eventicus:event=12345\'.\r\nAfter adding the tag your photo should appear automatically on the event page.\r\n\r\nAs an example you can tak a look at this event: <a href=\"http://eventicus.de/event/16\">2. Web Montag</a>\r\n\r\nI hope you enjoy this new feature. There is still more to come in the near future.','2007-06-07 12:21:56',NULL,4),(3,'We want your comments','As you might have noticed, you are able to comment on our blog now. We think this is a good way for our users to provide direct feedback on new features of Eventicus and on our blog posts.\r\nWe are also working on internationalization and hope that we can release a German version of Eventicus within the next two months.\r\nAnd we have some really interesting ideas for more and better community functions. So stay tuned for the things to come.','2007-07-05 18:37:56',NULL,4),(4,'We had some problems...','As you might have noticed we had some problems with our server. The site was not accessable for the last four days.\r\n\r\nWe apologize for the caused inconveniences. The server should run smoothly now and we hope that you enjoy using eventicus nevertheless.','2007-08-08 17:54:08',NULL,1),(5,'Now with iCalendar support','You want to see all eventicus events in your own Google Calendar or maybe in Mozilla Sunbird? \r\n\r\nNo Problem anymore because we added a little icon right beside the title of each event list page. The icon says \'ICAL\' and points you directly to an calendar readable format which can be imported into every calendar application with iCalendar support.\r\n\r\nYou only want all the events from Hanover, Germany? You get them with this icalendar url: <a href=\"http://eventicus.de/ical/events/1\">Hanover events</a>\r\n\r\nWe are are working on more iCalendar features so keep an eye on this blog for more updates.','2007-08-22 12:26:32',NULL,1),(6,'Events suchen und als HTML, RSS oder iCal ausgeben','Ich habe in den letzten Tagen einige neue Features in eventicus eingebaut. \r\n\r\nUnter anderem habe ich die Suche verbessert und ausgebaut. Ihr kÃ¶nnt nun nach Veranstaltungen suchen und euch das Suchergebnis wahlweise als HTML Seite sowie als RSS oder iCal Feeds ausgeben lassen.\r\n\r\nWenn ihr zum Beispiel alle Veranstaltungen sehen wollt, die den Suchbegriff \'Hamburg\' enthalten, kÃ¶nnt ihr entweder das Suchfeld oben verwenden, oder direkt folgende URL eingeben:\r\n\r\nhttp://eventicus.de/events/search/hamburg\r\n\r\nWollt ihr das Ergebnis lieber als RSS erhalten, Ã¤ndert ihr die URL einfach folgendermaÃŸen ab:\r\n\r\nhttp://eventicus.de/rss/search/hamburg\r\n\r\nUnd wollt ihr lieber alles im iCal Format haben, dann versucht einfach folgende URL:\r\n\r\nhttp://eventicus.de/ical/search/hamburg\r\n\r\nDamit sollte es nun auch leicht mÃ¶glich sein, die so gefundenen Veranstaltungen leicht in eure eigene Webseite einbinden zu kÃ¶nnen. Ein paar Programmierkenntnisse natÃ¼rlich vorausgesetzt. :)\r\n\r\nAber ein leicht zu verwendendes Widget zur einfachen Anzeige der Suchergebnisse in euren Seiten habe ich bereits auf meiner ToDo Liste - womit das Ganze dann auch ohne Programmierkenntnisse mÃ¶glich wÃ¤re.','2007-09-20 13:59:49',NULL,4),(7,'Downtime and Updates','As some of you might have noticed that we had some downtime over the last 24 hours. This was due to some upgrades on our server. We are changing our deployment strategy and had to modify some scripts and software on the server. We are now using Capistrano to deploy new versions of the eventicus application. I think this will help us to deploy new features more quickly. And if there are problems with an update we can always go back to a previous revision.\r\n\r\nBut there are some more news to come.\r\n\r\nWe are preparing for a mature update with new features such as timezone support, internationalization and some cool event import functionalities. But more about that later.\r\n\r\nSo stay tuned and enjoy eventicus.','2007-09-28 18:12:23',NULL,4);
